# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## What This Is

The `~/.augment` directory is the configuration home for **Augment AI (Auggie CLI)**, enhanced with the **PAI system v3.0-auggie** — an adaptation of Daniel Miessler's [Personal AI Infrastructure (PAI)](https://github.com/danielmiessler/PAI) v4.0 (Algorithm v3.7.0), tailored for the Augment CLI environment.

## PAI System Architecture

### Core Algorithm (`rules/algorithm.md`)
The PAI Algorithm v3.0-auggie (synced with PAI v3.7.0) is injected into every prompt (all user rules auto-apply). It enforces a 7-phase loop:

**OBSERVE → THINK → PLAN → BUILD → EXECUTE → VERIFY → LEARN**

- **Mode Selection**: NATIVE (quick <2min) | ALGORITHM (complex) | MINIMAL (greetings)
- **ISC (Ideal State Criteria)**: Atomic, binary-testable criteria with the Splitting Test
- **ISC Count Gate**: Criteria ranges per effort tier (Standard: 8-16, Extended: 16-32, etc.)
- **Capability Selection**: Skills selected during OBSERVE, applied during BUILD/EXECUTE
- **PRD as System of Record**: Written to `.prd/PRD-{YYYYMMDD}-{slug}.md`
- **Memory Capture**: LEARN phase writes to `MEMORY/LEARNING/reflections.jsonl`

### Skills (`skills/{name}/SKILL.md`)
Each skill is a subdirectory containing a `SKILL.md` with `name`/`description` frontmatter (agentskills.io format). The algorithm reads and applies them during BUILD/EXECUTE.

| Category | Skills |
|----------|--------|
| **Thinking** | first-principles, council, red-team, iterative-depth, science |
| **Research** | quick-research, standard-research, deep-investigation, extract-knowledge |
| **Security** | recon, web-assessment, threat-model, prompt-injection |
| **Content** | extract-wisdom |
| **Personas** | engineer (Marcus Webb), architect (Serena Blackwood), qa-tester (Quinn Torres), pentester (Rook Blackburn) |

### Slash Commands (`commands/`)
Invocable via `/<name>` in Auggie:
- `/think <skill> <topic>` — Apply a thinking methodology
- `/research <mode> <topic>` — Run research (quick/standard/deep/extract)
- `/assess <type> <target>` — Security assessment (recon/web/threat-model/prompt-injection)
- `/agent <persona> <task>` — Adopt an agent persona
- `/memory <operation>` — Memory operations (read/corrections/patterns/status/reflect)
- `/status` — Show PAI system status

### Hooks (in `settings.json`)
- **SessionStart**: Loads `MEMORY/STATE/current-work.json` at session start
- **Stop**: Prompts reflection writing if LEARN phase was skipped

### Memory System (`MEMORY/`)
- `LEARNING/reflections.jsonl` — LEARN phase reflections (auto-prompted by Stop hook)
- `LEARNING/corrections.jsonl` — User corrections captured during any phase
- `LEARNING/patterns.md` — Synthesized patterns from reflections
- `STATE/current-work.json` — Active work pointer (loaded by SessionStart hook)
- `RESEARCH/` — Persistent research output archive

### User Configuration (`USER/`)
- `ABOUTME.md` — Work identity (fill in your details)
- `AISTEERINGRULES.md` — AI behavior preferences
- `WORK/` — Company context and active project registry

### Rules (`rules/`)
All user rules are injected into every prompt regardless of frontmatter:
- `algorithm.md` — Core 7-phase algorithm (~370 lines)
- `security.md` — Security guidelines (~76 lines)
- `context-routing.md` — Topic-to-file routing table (~33 lines)

## MCP Servers (configure in settings.json)
Add your own MCP servers. Example:
- **claude-browser**: Playwright browser automation with your company service URLs (SSO, ticketing, wiki, monitoring)
- **monitoring**: Monitoring API (HTTP/OAuth)

## Security Notes
- `settings.json` contains plaintext credentials in MCP env vars — do not expose
- `session.json` contains API access token — do not expose
- Both files are excluded from git via `.gitignore`
